[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play] West's singleton diamond lead handed you the count: with West short, East had the length and therefore the queen, so the jack finesse was a near-certainty rather than a guess. A short-suit lead by one defender is the friendliest clue a two-way finesse can get. Nine tricks, beautifully read off the opening salvo.}
